Adaro, Bank Mandiri, Timah, Unilever: Indonesia Equity Preview

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-05-02T01:55:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-02/adaro-bank-mandiri-timah-unilever-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies may
have unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  gained 0.3 percent to 3,819.62.  PT Adaro Energy (ADRO IJ): Indonesia’s second-largest coal
producer said net income in the first quarter gained 11 percent
from a year earlier as prices of the fuel increased. Net income
in the three months ended March 31 rose to $109 million from $98
million a year earlier, the company said. Adaro fell 1.1 percent
to 2,200 rupiah.  PT Astra Agro Lestari (AALI IJ): Indonesia’s largest listed
plantation company by market value allocated 412 billion rupiah
($48 million) to 516 billion rupiah to build four palm-oil
processing plants,  Bisnis Indonesia  reported. Astra Agro was
unchanged at 23,150 rupiah.  PT Bank Danamon Indonesia (BDMN IJ): The bank that is owned
by Temasek Holdings Pte and Deutsche Bank AG said first-quarter
net income climbed 9 percent from a year earlier to 763 billion
rupiah. Danamon was unchanged at 6,200 rupiah.  PT Bank Mandiri (BMRI IJ):  Indonesia ’s biggest bank by
assets said first-quarter net income rose 89 percent from a year
earlier as lending expanded and after it sold a stake in state
airline PT Garuda Indonesia. Net income in the three months
ended March 31 rose to 3.78 trillion rupiah, the bank said.
Mandiri advanced 1.4 percent to 7,150 rupiah.  PT Timah (TINS IJ): Indonesia’s largest tin producer said
first-quarter net income jumped 150 percent from a year earlier
to 354.7 billion rupiah after the price of the metal increased.
Timah was unchanged at 2,875 rupiah.  PT Unilever Indonesia (UNVR IJ): The nation’s biggest
detergent maker said first-quarter net income climbed to 998.1
billion rupiah from 970.56 billion rupiah a year earlier.
Unilever was unchanged at 15,300 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
